        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix kfilnd threading",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix kfilnd threading\n\nThe current thread work pool implementation was unable to scale when a\nhigh rate of events occurred. The end result was all worker threads\nwere consumed and new events were dropped since they were unable to be\nprocessed.\n\nThe new approach allocates a \"pool\" of work items for each CQ and EQ.\nWhen an event occurs, the pool of work items are scheduled on a kfilnd\nwork queue. For the CQ, the pool work items are mapped to cores in the\ncorresponding CPT. For the CQ, the end result is multiple work queue\nthreads within the CPT processing the CQ until it is empty. For the\nEQ, since no CPT is assigned to the EQ, the EQ thread is not assigned\nto a specific core.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-9288\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Ia8060a84dd5d1e0ebbe22127c6fd4ed0ea8ffb64\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
